Chelsea midfielder Mason Mount is a major injury doubt for Saturday’s Premier League clash against Crystal Palace. Mount has started every league match for Chelsea this season. He’s returned with four goals and two assists in 11 games. However, Mount may miss his first league game of the season against the Eagles following an injury on Tuesday night. Against Ajax, Mount exited the game on the hour mark with an ankle injury. He was replaced by Callum Hudson-Odoi. Mason Mount ankle injury vs Ajax Mount appeared to roll his ankle after a tackle from Donny van der Beek.  Donny van der Beek tackle vs Mason Mount After the match, Frank Lampard spoke about Mount’s injury. The Chelsea boss said: They’ve strapped his ankle and hopefully it’s relatively minor but it’s one for the morning. One of the games of the season so far. Chelsea rallied from 4-1 down to draw 4-4 with Ajax in the Champions League. A Tammy Abraham own goal put Ajax ahead, before Jorginho scored from the penalty spot after 5 minutes. Goals from Quincy Promes, a Kepa Arrizabalaga own goal and another from Donny van de Beek put Ajax 4-1 up in the 55th minute. Cesar Azpilicueta scored Chelsea’s second, before the match turned with two red cards to Ajax’s two centre-halves in 10 seconds. Both Daley Blind and Joel Veltman were dismissed for second yellow cards.   Blind Justice. 🙈 . Before receiving his second yellow card and ultimately a red card, Ajax's Daley #Blind was brought down by Christian #Pulisic, was it a foul? . It was the first of two red cards in ten seconds for Ajax. . . . #CHEARS #Ajax #UCL #ChampionsLeague #footballtime A post shared by  Optus Sport (@optussport) on Nov 5, 2019 at 9:45pm PST //www.instagram.com/embed.js Against 9-men, Chelsea levelled through Jorginho and Reece James. And, in dramatic fashion, VAR chalked off a fifth Chelsea goal after the ball hit Tammy Abraham’s hand in the build-up. After the match, Ajax playmaker Dusan Tadic fumed about how the officials handled the match against Chelsea. Tadic argued that Ajax had suffered a triple injustice at Stamford Bridge. The Serb complained that Italian referee Gianluca Rocchi “stole everything from us”. Tadic argued that Blind and Veltman’s second yellow cards were both unfair, and Chelsea’s penalty was another injustice.   “I’ve never seen in my life triple punishment!” 🤯 . . @dt10_official’s incredible rant at the referee following @afcajax’s thrilling 4-4 draw with @chelseafc 😅👀 . . . . . . . . . . .#tadic #angry #football #chelsea #ajax A post shared by  HaytersTV (@hayterstv) on Nov 5, 2019 at 3:20pm PST //www.instagram.com/embed.js See also: Atalanta vs Manchester City betting tips: Champions League match preview & predictions Crvena Zvezda vs Tottenham betting tips: Champions League match preview & predictions Source: Great Goals